Run a build wave for Northstar Research.

Usage: /wave <wave-number>

Waves:
  0 - Shared Foundation (northstar-models, northstar-llm, northstar-vector, northstar-db packages)
  1 - Infrastructure (docker-compose, .env, migrations, Dockerfiles, CI, Makefile)
  2 - Three Services (research-agent :8099, research-portal :3010, chat-import-bridge :3022)
  3 - Tests + Hardening (unit/integration/E2E tests, backup/restore scripts, CLI tools)

Before executing:
  1. Read contracts/BUILD_CONTRACT.md
  2. Read BUILD_PLAN.md for the wave details
  3. Spawn parallel sub-agents per the plan
  4. After completion, update contracts/BUILD_CONTRACT.md

Examples:
  /wave 0     - Build shared foundation packages
  /wave 1     - Build infrastructure
  /wave 2     - Build all three services
  /wave 3     - Build tests and hardening
